HEADWORD: Sephardim
<hw>Se*phar"dim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NHeb.; orig.
uncert.]</ety> <def>Jews who are descendants of the former Jews of Spain
and Portugal. They are as a rule darker than the northern Jews, and have
more delicate features.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sephen</ent>⟦br⟧
